#!/bin/bash

build() {
  add_runscript
}

help() {
  cat <<'EOF'
Prefers an inserted Thorch SD root over the root UUID embedded in /KERNEL.

The runtime hook looks for the expected Thorch SD image shape: a two-partition
mmcblk disk with a vfat ROCKNIX boot partition and an ext4 or btrfs THORCH_ROOT
root partition. Pass thorch.sdprefer=0 on the kernel command line to disable
it, or thorch.sdwait=<seconds> to change the short detection wait.
EOF
}
